      /EJECT
      *****************************************************************
      ** +--- Start of Main processing -----------------------------------+
      ** ¦                                                                ¦
      ** ¦ Initial processing is performed automatically: the             ¦
      ** ¦ executed at program activation.                                ¦
      ** ¦                                                                ¦
      ** +----------------------------------------------------------------+
      *
      * Main processing
      *
     C                   EXSR      MAIN
      *
      * Return
      *
     C     @INKC         IFEQ      '1'
     C                   SETON                                        LR
     C                   END
     C                   RETURN
      *
      *****************************************************************
      /EJECT
      *****************************************************************
      * MAIN - MAIN processing
      *****************************************************************
     C     MAIN          BEGSR
      *
     C                   MOVEA     OKSecDets     @EI
      *
      * SET SCREEN ERROR INDICATOR ACCORDING TO STATUS OF 'OK' FLAG
      *
     C                   Z-ADD     1             C                 2 0
     C                   Z-ADD     10            E                 2 0
      *
     C     C             DOUGT     60
     C     @EI(C)        IFEQ      'N'
     C     @EI(C)        OREQ      'W'
     C                   MOVEL     '1'           *IN(E)
     C                   END
     C                   ADD       1             C
     C                   ADD       1             E
     C                   END


      ** Set up the customer reference to be used by the message handler
     C                   EVAL      TranRef = DDCSST
     C                   EVAL      ActionCode = 'I'

      **--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
      ** The following /COPY line includes processing for the error and
      ** warning messages.
     D/COPY ZACPYSRC,MSGHNDDSP1
      **--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
      *
      * ENABLE FUNCTION KEYS
      *
      *
      * Write message subfile, key details and footer screen
      *
     C                   TIME                    DDTIME
     C                   WRITE     SDSECDKS0
     C                   WRITE     SDSECDKD1
     C                   WRITE     SDSECDKF1
     C                   READ      SDSECDKD1                              99
      *
      * Clear message subfile
      *
      * Set screen error indicator off
      *
     C                   MOVEA     @Z0           *IN(10)
      *
      * Set return keys
      *
     C                   MOVE      *INKC         @INKC
     C                   MOVE      *INKG         @INKG
     C                   MOVE      *INKH         @INKH
     C                   MOVE      *INKL         @INKL
      *
     C                   ENDSR

      **--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
      ** The following /COPY line includes the ProcMsgs subroutine
      ** to process error and warning messages.
     D/COPY ZACPYSRC,MSGHNDDSP2
      **--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

      ********************************************************************
      /EJECT
      *****************************************************************
      * *INZSR - INITIAL PROCESSING
      *****************************************************************
     C     *INZSR        BEGSR
      *
      ** Parameters
      *
     C     *ENTRY        PLIST
      *
      * INPUT PARAMETERS :
      * Return code
     C                   PARM                    RetCodeIn

      * Customer Number / Shortname
     C                   PARM                    DDCSST

      ** Security Details in screen format
     C                   PARM                    SecDets

      ** Security Details OK indicators
     C                   PARM                    OKSecDets

      * ERRORS
     C                   PARM                    FldNameArr
     C                   PARM                    MsgIdArr
     C                   PARM                    MsgDtaArr

      * OUTPUT PARAMETERS :

      * Function Keys
     C                   PARM                    @INKC             1
     C                   PARM                    @INKG             1
     C                   PARM                    @INKH             1
     C                   PARM                    @INKL             1


      ** Initialize program name

     C                   MOVEL     'SDSECDKDSP'  DBPGM

      ** Move user and workstation ID to screen fields.

     C                   MOVEL     PsUser        DDUSER
     C                   MOVEL     PsJobName     DDWID
      *
     C                   MOVE      '1'           *IN97
     C                   MOVEL     '*'           DDPGMQ
      *
      ** ACCESS BANK DETAILS
      *
     C                   CALL      'AOBANKR0'
     C                   PARM      *BLANKS       @RTCD             7
     C                   PARM      '*FIRST '     @OPTN             7
     C     SDBANK        PARM      SDBANK        DSFDY
      *
      * DATABASE ERROR
      *
     C     @RTCD         IFNE      *BLANKS
     C                   MOVEL     'SDBANKPD'    DBFILE
     C                   MOVEL     '900'         DBASE
     C                   MOVEL     @OPTN         DBKEY
     C                   EXSR      *PSSR
     C                   END
      *
      *
      **--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
      ** The following /COPY line sets up the fixed data for SD *DSP
      ** functions for the message handler, ZAMSGHNDLE.
     D/COPY SDCPYSRC,MSGHNDDATA
      **--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


     C                   ENDSR

